data.title: Coinbase CEO's live prediction market bets during Q3 earnings call earns praise, shares up 5%. Revenue: $1.9 billion.
data.description: Shares of Coinbase Global Inc. (NASDAQ: COIN) saw a 5% increase in premarket trading on Friday following CEO Brian Armstrong's unconventional move during the third-quarter earnings call. Armstrong read live prediction market bets at the end of the call, prompting positive reactions from listeners and earning praise from investor Anthony Pompliano. The incident was hailed as one of the most authentic moments in corporate earnings. This public display showcased Armstrong's influence in promoting transparency and engagement in the crypto community. In terms of financial performance, Coinbase reported a significant 25% revenue growth in Q3 2025, with earnings reaching $1.9 billion. As a further display of confidence in the digital currency, the company expanded its Bitcoin holdings.

data.title: SPS Commerce reports Q3 earnings of $1.13 per share, sales of $189.904 million, cutting FY25 guidance below estimates.
data.description: SPS Commerce, Inc. (NASDAQ: SPSC) released its third-quarter financial results, showing a mix of performance. The company's quarterly earnings stood at $1.13 per share, surpassing the analyst consensus of $1.00 per share. However, quarterly sales were reported at $189.904 million, falling short of the expected $191.797 million. Looking forward, the company provided fourth-quarter guidance below market estimates, with projected adjusted EPS in the range of $0.98-$1.02, compared to the anticipated $1.05. Sales for the upcoming quarter are forecasted to be between $192.700 million and $194.700 million, while analysts expected $199.897 million. CEO Chad Collins mentioned that retailers and trading partners are increasingly focusing on collaboration and automation in their operations. In addition, the company lowered its full-year 2025 sales guidance below estimates.

data.title: Chevron reports Q3 2025 results; adjusted earnings at $1.85/share & sales at $49.7 billion exceed Wall Street estimates. Reported earnings fell to $3.5 billion. Acquisition impacts oil output.
data.description: Chevron Corp. (NYSE CVX) released its third-quarter 2025 financial results, revealing adjusted earnings of $1.85 per share, surpassing Wall Street expectations of $1.71. Sales for the quarter stood at $49.7 billion, exceeding the anticipated $49.0 billion. Reported earnings declined to $3.5 billion ($1.82 per share) from $4.5 billion ($2.48 per share) the previous year. Factors contributing to this drop included lower crude oil prices, severance costs, and transaction expenses linked to the Hess acquisition. Cash flow from operations also decreased to $9.4 billion from $9.7 billion. More details are available on Benzinga.com.

data.title: "Who's Who of Asian Women 2025" directory on ResearchAndMarkets.com lists thousands of entries, reflecting the increasing role of women in Asia, a one-stop research tool with extensive indexing.
data.description: Dublin-based ResearchAndMarkets.com has recently introduced the "Who's Who of Asian Women 2025" directory. This updated edition encompasses thousands of profiles representing diverse backgrounds, highlighting the increasing influence of women in modern Asia. Serving as a comprehensive research aid, the directory facilitates quick and convenient referencing with its detailed indexing. It acknowledges both established figures and emerging female leaders. Each entry in the directory includes essential information like the individual's date of prominence, making it a valuable resource for those interested in prominent women in Asia.

data.title: AKVA group ASA has started buying back up to 60,000 of its own shares for employee share programme.
data.description: On September 23, 2025, AKVA Group ASA, also known as AKVA Group, disclosed the commencement of the repurchase of a maximum of 60,000 of their own shares. The purpose of this buyback is to utilize them in the company's share program designed for employees.

data.title: Jefferson Place Apartments in Lake Hopatcong, N.J., launching hardhat tours for prospective tenants before its official opening.
data.description: In Lake Hopatcong, New Jersey, on October 30, 2025, Jefferson Place Apartments has exciting news to share. They are introducing exclusive hardhat tours for potential tenants to get a special sneak peek at their upscale community before its grand opening to the public.

data.title: Cloudflare (NYSE: NET) beats Q3 earnings with 27 cents per share, revenue at $562.02 million, exceeding analyst estimates.
data.description: Cloudflare Inc. exceeded analysts' expectations for the third quarter with a better-than-expected performance. The company reported earnings of 27 cents per share, surpassing the estimated 23 cents. Additionally, Cloudflare achieved quarterly revenue of $562.02 million, exceeding the projected $544.82 million. This marked a 31% year-over-year revenue growth, showcasing the company's increasing momentum. The CEO, Matthew, highlighted the results as a demonstration of the company's commitment to innovation and execution.

data.title: Oppenheimer Holdings Inc. reported Q3 2025 earnings of $21.7 million, $2.06 EPS, down from $24.5 million, $2.38 EPS.
data.description: On October 31, 2025, Oppenheimer Holdings Inc. (NYSE: OPY) announced their financial results for the third quarter of 2025. The company reported a net income of $21.7 million, translating to $2.06 per basic earnings per share. This figure marked a decrease from the previous quarter where the net income was $24.5 million, or $2.38 per basic earnings per share.

data.title: Joby Aviation begins manufacturing propeller blades in Dayton, Ohio facility, expanding in-house production for electric air taxis.
data.description: A company, Joby Aviation, known for electric air taxis, revealed manufacturing has started for propeller blades at its Dayton, Ohio facility. This move aims to enhance in-house production of a key component and complements testing activities in Ohio. Dayton has a significant aviation history and will play a crucial role in production as the company gears up for the commercial launch. Joby Aviation, listed on the NYSE as JOBY, is making strides as it prepares for taking its passenger service to the skies.
